node.text: It was a beautiful day and I’m in love with my new daughter-in-law. Check out this video shot and produced by Stephen Norregaard. See the full wide format version here: https://vimeo.com/308998543

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on August 30, 2021 tagging @stofferhome. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Some people actually spend quite a bit of time in the powder room. 😬 So why not make it nice, right? #jsdenglishcottage  Mirror is antique. Sconces from @stofferhome My husband and I built the brass base with railing parts. You didn’t know I was a DIY’er did you??

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on August 29, 2021 tagging @stofferhome, and @stofferhomecabinetry. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text: One of my faves. The #jsd1902victorian is small and layered with architectural goodness. Cabinetry is in Kensington Taupe and Eastbourne from @stofferhomecabinetry Lighting, hardware and accessories from @stofferhome Photographed by @stofferphotographyinteriors .

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on August 26, 2021 tagging @sherwinwilliams. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: It’s raining and I love it. We really need it and the clouds make our dining room at The Madison all dark and moody. Maybe we should light some candles and have dinner in there!  Paint color is Grizzle Gray from @sherwinwilliams

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on August 25, 2021 tagging @stofferhome, and @stofferhomecabinetry. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: A little swipe action to see one the most simple and timeless kitchens we’ve done. The #jsdenglishcottage which was my old house before moving to The Madison. 😍 The cabinetry is in Kensington Taupe from @stofferhomecabinetry and you can find all the hardware and lighting @stofferhome Photographed with natural light only on an extremely gray January day by the talented duo @johnstoffer and @maurastoffer

node.text: #samsunghomeappliances #sponsored I specified this Extra-Large Capacity Smart Dial Front Loading Washer and Dryer in Brushed Black from @samsungus for @grace_start because when you have four little kids, laundry is kind of your life.  I thought she would appreciate the huge capacity and the Wi-Fi connectivity that allows her to start, stop and schedule cycles and more, right from her smartphone.  And the fact that they are so fantastic looking is the icing on the cake.  Good move overall.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on August 16, 2021 tagging @stofferhome, and @stofferhomecabinetry. May be an image of furniture, brick wall and indoor.

node.text: Often times, in ok’d homes the kitchen is located in the back corner of the house, typically on the north side. The parts of the house with better natural light was for important rooms like formal dining rooms and living rooms. The kitchen at The Madison is no exception. So I converted that north corner space into a breakfast room and coffee bar. See the wallpapered bumped out wall in the before pics?  That’s the brick chimney you see in the after pics!  Photographed by @stofferphotographyinteriors Remodeled by @kenowabuilders Sources are tagged.

node.text: I’m opening up the windows on this perfect Michigan Sunday afternoon. I just want to keep saying “Ahhhh” as I sit  Take a moment today. It’s good for you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on August 12, 2021 tagging @kohler, @rejuvenation, @stofferphotographyinteriors, and @stofferhome. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Our client found this sink at an architectural salvage yard. When he called to see if it could work anywhere in their project, I didn’t even need to think. “We’ll find a place!” I said. And here it is!  In the guest bath at the #jsdadamodernclassic  Photographed by @stofferphotographyinteriors Remodeled by @kenowabuilders Mirror by @rejuvenation

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jean Stoffer on August 11, 2021 tagging @kohler, @annsacks, @stofferphotographyinteriors, and @stofferhome. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: I loved designing this bathroom. The tile options available now allow for so much creativity!  I found this amazing tile @annsacks. I think the combo of the antique mirror and traditional vanities with modern sconces and tile is what makes this room sing!  Photography by @stofferphotographyinteriors Remodeling by @kenowabuilders
